Merge branch 'dmg'

According to luks py2app still isn't fixed
so this is necessary for Picard.

See pull request #42
and issue #43

implemented upstream
(since sphinx 1.2, 2013-12-10)

enable syntax highlighting in README/GitHub

idea from alastair/python-musicbrainzngs#163

fix ResourceWarning in setup.py

found with python -Wd setup.py test
also test for python 3.4

darwin: check if running in bundle/dmg

According to a built picard dmg the dylib can't be found
in ./Content/Frameworks/

This adds an extra check for ../Frameworks
fix typo in comment

use new urls for python-musicbrainzngs

The urls follow the actual name of the package now.
print device used in complex example

see pull request #41
(make examples usable for non-Linux users)

Minor change for out of box Windows support.
Default device in readme and example.py

set version to 1.1.0
update CHANGES

Merge branch 'toc_string'

see pull request #36

	test_discid.py

Merge branch 'deprecate_to_asserts'

see pull request #38

change tests for success to asserts

Success can only be false due to programming errors
on our end and invalid usage of python-discid.

However, we should in any way prevent a libdiscid segfault.
So we add asserts to fail early.
remove test_emptyness / TestClass
remove deprecated class discid.DiscId
set version to 1.1.0-dev
add more toc_string tests

This is part of the libdiscid 0.6.0 API
set version to 1.0.3, update CHANGES
